hey, so we’ve been attempting to get some automation going for TeleOp that can also work in autonomous and have been running into multiple of the same issue. Basically, every time we run the automation command to fire a note into the speaker, it errors out with ERROR 2 [CAN SPARK] IDs: 10, 11, 12, 13, timed out while waiting for Periodic Status 5 after disabling the robot and ERROR 2 [CAN SPARK] IDs: 10, 11, 12, 13, 20, timed out while waiting for Periodic Status 5 while the robot is running.

Things that may be useful to you people:

GitHub

GitHub - FRC1555/FRC2024Code: ZA CODE

ZA CODE. Contribute to FRC1555/FRC2024Code development by creating an account on GitHub.

(I included the most recent log file in the repository as well, if you need that)

Thanks in advance for any help!

Do the motors attached to SparkMAXs 10-13 and 20 stop working or do they work? i.e. Does your drivetrain continue to work?

The first thing that I would think if I saw that error message is that your CAN bus is disconnected in between one of those motors and the rest of the bus.
